If the string is "1234", the possible permutations are 24 i.e. (4!)
Based on the value of k, we can come to a conclusion about the first digit of the kth permutation

If k=6, the kth permutation of "1234" is "1432"
To get the answer -
-----> get the first_digit + do the operation on the remaining string with a new k

**How to calculate the first digit?**
If (K%(n-1)! == 0) --> then first element will be at ([k/(n-1)!] -1) index
else --> first element will be at [k/(n-1)!] index

example n=3, so string ="123" answer is "321" if k=6 and "312" if k=5
when k = 6 --> 6%2! is equal to 0. then the first  element is at ((6/2)- 1) i.e. at 2nd index ("3")
when k = 5 --> 5%2 is not equal to 0, then the first element is at 5/2 i.e 2nd index ("3)


after calculating the first digit, we can update the k and apply the same operation to the remaining string
**How to update k?**
if (K%(n-1)! == 0) --> k = (n-1)!
else --> k = k%(n-1)!

in the above example when k =6 --> k= (3-1)! = 2
when k = 5 --> k = 5%(3-1)! = 1
remaining string = "12"

For second element --> 
k becomes 2 (for k=6) -- 2%1! is equal to 0, then second element is at index 2/1 -1 i.e. 1 ("2")
k becomes 1 (for k=5) -- 1%1! is equal to 0, then second element is at index 1/1 -1 i.e. 0 ("1")

when n=1
we have to add it in the answer and return the answer

```
class Solution {
    public String getPermutation(int n, int k) {
        String s = "";
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            s = s + i;
        }
        return permutation(s, k);
    }

    static String permutation(String s, int k){
        String str = "";
        int n = s.length();
        int ind=-1;
        int factorial = fact(n);

		while (n>1){
            factorial /= n;
            if (k%factorial == 0){
                ind = (k/factorial) -1;
                char first_ele = s.charAt(ind);
                str += first_ele;
                k = factorial;
            }
            else {
                ind = k/factorial;
                char first_ele = s.charAt(ind);
                str += first_ele;
                k = k%factorial;
            }
            s = s.substring(0, ind) + s.substring(ind+1);
            n--;

        }

        return str + s;
    }

    static int fact(int n){
        if (n<=1){
            return 1;
        }
        return n*fact(n-1);
    }
}
```

