I was stuck in this question for quite awhile and then it hit me. So, i tried to solve this question using a stack.
Push the nodes (not values) of each linked list into a separate stack. After the intersection point, the nodes will be the same.
While the stacks are not empty and the top of each stack is the same, pop from each stack.
When the tops are not equal, the previously popped element (the last equal node) was the intersection point.

Here is the code for it:
``` 
class Solution {
public:
    ListNode *getIntersectionNode(ListNode *headA, ListNode *headB) {
        stack<ListNode*> A, B;
        ListNode *ptr1=headA, *ptr2=headB, *lastRead=NULL;
        while(ptr1) {
            A.push(ptr1);
            ptr1=ptr1->next;
        }
        while(ptr2) {
            B.push(ptr2);
            ptr2=ptr2->next;
        }
        while(!A.empty() && !B.empty() && (A.top()==B.top())) {
            lastRead=A.top();
            A.pop();
            B.pop();

        }
        return lastRead;
    }
};
```
Hope this helped :)

