# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
- Compare on the basis of length
- The one which is longer, traverse it until the length become equal in both
- After that we'll traverse each listnode one by one, if both heads (headA and headB) collides return that listnode.
- Else return null, no intersection.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
- The base case if definitely if any of the head is NULL,
-  Return NULL, i.e no intersection.
- For comparing we can implement a separate function.
- Then implement as intution says.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(m+n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(1)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
