# Intuition
We will use maps to solve this one.

# Approach
- Create an unordered_map of ListNode* and let's just take int for the value.
- then transfer all the nodes of first LL in the map.
- then traverse the seconf LL and check if a node from second LL is present in the map.
- if there is one node present, then return that one.
- else there is no intersection in the linked list, so return NULL.

# Code
```
/**
 * Definition for singly-linked list.
 * struct ListNode {
 *     int val;
 *     ListNode *next;
 *     ListNode(int x) : val(x), next(NULL) {}
 * };
 */
class Solution {
public:
    ListNode *getIntersectionNode(ListNode *headA, ListNode *headB) {
        unordered_map<ListNode*, int> mp;

        ListNode* temp = headA;

        //LL A nodes stored inside the map
        while(temp){
            mp[temp]++;
            temp = temp->next;
        }

        //LL B traversal
        temp = headB;
        while(temp){
            if(mp.find(temp) != mp.end())
                return temp;

            temp = temp->next;
        }

        return NULL;
    }
};
```

