solutions.content:
Both have O(n) time complexity

### O(1) Space Solution - Bit Manipulation
How to handle this  with O(1) space? Lets see
>Before going let us see XOR property.
>If both bits are same the give x^y = 0 
>If both bit are different we get x^y = 1 
>Here x and y are the individual bits and not the number

FIrst lets take XOR of the entire array - what will be the output?
It will be the XOR of the two unique numbers.
Suppose the array is - 1,1,2,2,3,5 
XOR will be 3^5 = 6 ``(011 ^ 101 = 110)``

Now what to do with this number? As we can see the set bits are the ones which are different in both the numbers.
Lets choose one bit from this result.
So if consider all numbers in array we can classify the numbers in two category 
1. Group with the bit **set** at the chosen position
2. Group with the bit **unset** at the chosen position

And if we perform XOR of both the group the repeating numbers will cancel each other out. So we will get those individual numbers in the seperate groups.

So for above example if we choose the first set bit from the right i.e. the  bit in the middle
1 - 001
2 - 010
3 - 011
5 - 101
``Array  = [1,1,2,2,3,5]``
Group A (middle bit set) = 2,2,3 -> XOR = 3
Group B (middle bit unset) = 1,1,5 -> XOR = 5

If you still have doubt: Ofcourse they both will end up in different group as the bit we chose is from their XOR and so for one of them it is set and for the other it is unset.

> #### For those who are not accustomed to bit manipulation
> if x = 1:   0000001
> x<<1  will be  - 0000010
> again x<<1 will be 0000100
> You get the idea, its also the powers of two as they are binary numbers.
> To check if a current bit is set you perform & operation
> So our xor was 6 : 110 
> to find set bit let x = 001 initially
> 6^x = (110 ^ 001) = 0 so perfrom x<<1 => x = 010
> Now 6^x = (111 ^ 010) = 1 - This is the rightmost set bit

CODE: 
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> singleNumber(vector<int>& nums) {
        int xr = 0,num1=0,num2=0;  // Xor of entire array, the two numbers
        for(int x: nums) xr^=x;   // XOR of two num
        int setBit = 1;   // Let us begin with the first num
        for(int i = 1;i<=31;i++){
            if(xr & setBit) break;    //This is the rightmost set bit   
            setBit<<=1;
        }

        for(int x: nums){
            if((x&setBit) == setBit) num1 ^= x;   // this is group A
            else num2 ^= x;   // This is group B
        }
        return {num1,num2};
    }
};
```
