**we will be given numbers which all will be repeating except two numbers so the best way to identify these numbers is using finding the low-bit.**

Now what a low bit is ??

**for ex: [1,2,1,3,2,5]**
**low bit is the 2's complement of the sum**

How do we find a sum??

Sum = 0;
sum ^= nums[i];

after finding sum we find low bit of it using sum & (-sum)

Now we divide the our results which comprises of two numbers into different categories.
One with having low bit and other not.

Let's see the code:

```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> singleNumber(vector<int>& nums) {

        int sum = 0;
        for (auto num : nums) {
            sum ^= num;
        }

        vector<int> res{0, 0};
        int lowbit = sum & (-sum);  //way to find lowbit
        for (auto num : nums) {
            if (num & lowbit)
                res[0] ^= num;
            else
                res[1] ^= num;
        }
        return res;
    }
};
```

