**Explanation:**
We use a set to indicate which numbers we already saw.
If the current number is already in the set, we remove it.
Otherwise, we add it.
Because each number appears exactly once, at the end we will end up removing all the numbers that appear twice and will be left with the two numbers that appear only once.

