```
We have to find the 2 unique number using XOR operation but need 2 pass.
1. First XOR all elements and we get the XOR of 2 unique elements. We can get the bit difference of 2 number
from the right most set bit of XOR number.
2. Then we can group the numbers based on the right most set bit of the XOR and all numbers have the set
bit will be in one group and others without set bit will be in another group and also the 2 unique numbers
will be in the two other groups. Taking XOR of 2 different group will give us 2 unique numbers.

Example : nums = [1,2,1,3,2,5], XOR = 6 (110), Setbit in position 1 and bit mask = 10
Left group with Setbit => [2,3,2] => Left XOR = 2 ^ 3 ^ 2 = 3
Right group without Setbit => [1,1,5] => Right XOR = 1 ^ 1 ^ 5 = 5
```

```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> singleNumber(vector<int>& nums) {

        // total XOR of nums array
        int txor = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<nums.size();i++)txor^=nums[i];

        // get bit mask of right most set bit of txor 
        int mask = 1;
        while((txor&mask)==0)mask = mask<<1;

        // 2 unique numbers in nums array
        int a = 0; int b = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<nums.size();i++)
        {
            // right group without Setbit and their XOR 
            if((nums[i]&mask)==0)a^=nums[i];

            // left group with Setbit and their XOR
            else b^=nums[i];
        }

        return {a,b};        
    }
};
```

