**This is a question of Bitwise Manipulation**.
******
**Time Complexity** : O(n)
**Space Complexity** : O(1)

**CORNER CASE** : if nums array has -2147483648 as a value, so decrement this value will create Runtime Error of overflow. That's why it is advised to use unsigned long long.


```
class Solution {
	public:
		vector<int> singleNumber(vector<int>& nums) {
			// We want to find two elements u & v
			unsigned long long ans=0; // int will give Runtime Error 
			int n=nums.size();

			for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
				ans^=nums[i];   //ans = XOR of all elements = u XOR v 
			}

			//We want to segregate u & v
			unsigned long long temp = ans & (~(ans-1)); // ans-1 will make minimum value(if int) out of bound
			// captures one bit of ans variable
			//which will differentiate both u & v 
			int zero_partition=0,nonzero_partition=0;

			for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
				if((temp & nums[i]) == 0) 
					zero_partition^=nums[i]; //all even occuring element will become zero
				else
					nonzero_partition^=nums[i]; //all even occuring element will become zero
			}
			vector<int> result;

			result.push_back(nonzero_partition);
			result.push_back(zero_partition);

			return result;

		}
	};
```

**For example:**
****
*nums* = [1,2,1,3,2,5]

*ans* = 1 XOR 2 XOR 1 XOR 3 XOR 2 XOR 5 = 3 XOR 5 = 6(0110)

We want to segregate 3 & 5 from 6.
*temp* = 6 & (~5) = 6 AND (NOT 5)

0110 =   6
1010 = (~5)
_____
0010 = 2
_____

Traversing the nums array once again & *temp* = 2(0010)

	if (temp & nums[i])==0
		{1,1,5}
		zero_partition = 1 XOR 1 XOR 5 = 5

	else(i.e. not equal to zero)
		{2,2,3}
		nonzero_partition = 2 XOR 2 XOR 3 =3

We have separated 3 & 5 and next added to vector<int> result

*result* = [3,5]

