solutions.content:
Thinking Process:
1. There are two factors to determine this cache's delete and add: one is the visited frequence; the other is the adding time(when does it add). In order to better describe these important information, we customized a class, named Node to contain them. 
```java
	class Node {
    int key;
    int val;
    int count;
    int timer;
    public Node(int k, int v, int c, int t) {
        this.key = k;
        this.val = v;
        this.count = c;
        this.timer = t;
    }
}
```
2. When we determine which Node to be deleted, we need to know their orders. So we use PriorityQueue to help us to sort according to its count(visit frequence) and update time. 
	``new PriorityQueue<Node>(
        (a, b)->(a.count==b.count?(a.timer-b.timer):(a.count-b.count)));``
3. Meanwhile, in order to fasten search/get speed, we use HashMap to store all key-value information. 
4. There are two speical cases which we need to notice: 
	(1) when add the existed key-value, for example: (1,1) already in cache, and then we add (1,2). In this condition, this node's count should be old count plus 1, not just 1. And its timer should be updated. 

	``add(new Node(key, value, node.count+1, timer++));``

	(2) when two nodes have the same count/frequence, we need to use their timer to sort them.

Test cases:
1. cap: 0, // empty cache
2. cap:1, put(1,1), get(1), put(2,2), get(1) // normal case
3. cap: 1, put(1,1), put(1,2), get(1) // check count update case with adding
4. cap: 2, put(1,1), put(2,2), put(3, 3), get(1) // check timer update case
5. cap: 2, put(1,1), put(2,2), get(2), put(3,3), get(1) // check count update case with visit

Time Complexity: O(logn) for get, O(logn) for put. because when we get and put, we need to update PriorityQueue informaiton. For PriorityQueue, its insert and remove operations need O(logn). n is the size of PriorityQueue; For HashMap, its insert and remove need O(1). 

Space Complexity: O(n) , n is the cache's capacity. 

```java
class LFUCache {
    private Map<Integer, Node> map;
    private PriorityQueue<Node> pq;
    private int cap;
    private static int timer;
    public LFUCache(int capacity) {
        map = new HashMap();
        pq = new PriorityQueue<Node>(
            (a, b)->(a.count==b.count?(a.timer-b.timer):(a.count-b.count)));
        cap = capacity;
        timer = 0;
    }
    private void remove(Node node) {
        map.remove(node.key);
        pq.remove(node);
    }
    private void add(Node node) {
        map.put(node.key, node);
        pq.offer(node);
    }

    public int get(int key) {
        if (map.containsKey(key)) {
            Node node = map.get(key);
            remove(node);
            add(new Node(node.key, node.val, node.count+1, timer++));
            return node.val;
        } else return -1;
    }

    public void put(int key, int value) {
        if (map.containsKey(key)) {
            Node node = map.get(key);
            remove(node);
            add(new Node(key, value, node.count+1, timer++));
        } else {
            if (cap!=0) {
                if (map.size()==cap) remove(pq.peek());
                add(new Node(key, value, 1, timer++));
            }
        }
    }
}

class Node {
    int key;
    int val;
    int count;
    int timer;
    public Node(int k, int v, int c, int t) {
        this.key = k;
        this.val = v;
        this.count = c;
        this.timer = t;
    }
}
