solutions.content:
Simple concept:
Storing a LinkedList of Keys `KeyNode` inside a LinkedList of Frequencies `FreqNode`
`FreqNode` acts as frequency buckets that holds all Key/Value pairs that have that frequency. 

When updating a Key/Value pair:
1. Use `map.get(key)` to retrieve the `KeyNode`  
2. Remove the `KeyNode` from the `FreqNode` parent 
3. Move it to the `freq+1` node (ie. the `parent.next` node), OR create a new node if `parent.next.freq` > `freq+1` 

````
+---+      +---+      +---+      +---+      "FreqNode"
| 0 | ---> | 1 | ---> | 3 | ---> | 6 |      Frequency Buckets
+---+      +---+      +---+      +---+      
             |          |          |
           +---+      +---+      +---+      "KeyNode"
           |1,1|      |2,2|      |5,5|      Key/Value Pairs
		   +---+      +---+      +---+	    Ordered from Most Recently Used (Top) to Least Recently Used (Bottom)
             |          |                   Adding [6,6] would remove the Lest Frequent and Least Recent node [3,3]
           +---+      +---+
           |3,3|      |4,4|
		   +---+      +---+
````
If get(2) was called:
````
+---+      +---+      +---+      +---+      +---+ 
| 0 | ---> | 1 | ---> | 3 | ---> | 4 | ---> | 6 |   
+---+      +---+      +---+      +---+      +---+      
             |          |          |          |
           +---+      +---+      +---+      +---+ 
           |1,1|      |4,4|      |2,2|      |5,5|
		   +---+      +---+      +---+      +---+ 
             |          
           +---+ 
           |3,3| 
		   +---+ 
````
If get(4) was called: (Note that [4,4] was used most recently, so it's placed at the beginning of its respective Freq LinkedList)
````
+---+      +---+      +---+      +---+ 
| 0 | ---> | 1 | ---> | 4 | ---> | 6 | 
+---+      +---+      +---+      +---+      
             |          |          |
           +---+      +---+      +---+    
           |1,1|      |4,4|      |5,5| 
		   +---+      +---+      +---+	
             |          |               
           +---+      +---+
           |3,3|      |2,2|
		   +---+      +---+
````
