# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
I am using one map and set, set will keep track of frequency and counter.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
declare 4 member
1. unordere_map, key-> {val, frequecy, counter}
2. set, {frequecy, counter, key}
3. cap, max capacity of set
4. counter, will start from 0

Now for Get function, 
~ we first check if it's in map, if not return -1;
~ if present, then increase frequncy and update counter, by removing prevoius values from map

Now fro put function,
~ we first check if key, present in map, if present, then will update value, frequncy and counter same as Get function method
~if key not present, then will check if set is full, then will delete first element of set, because set holding freq as 0 index, counter 1
so if freq same, min counter at beginging, after deleting will insert new key

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
nlogc, where n is no. of keys, c is swt max capacity, because using set

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n), n is no. of keys

