Actually, at first, I tried to use a vector of double linked lists. However, although I can pass majority of the test cases, at least one of them will cause heap overflow. Therefore, we need to use linked lists.
When I first encounter this question, it seems quite strange to me. But in fact, the basic idea of LFU is the same as LRU, i.e. use linked list to reduce the run time of push_front() and erase() to O(1).
I would say there are many points in the implemenation that can lead to errors. But once you can do it, you should practice LFU more, until you can write it in limited time and bug-free. (Maybe during an interview LOL)

