The idea is similar to the one using DoubleLinkedList, but here we leverage the fact that javascript `Map()` construct are actually ordered and you can use `Map.values().next().value` to easily get the first inserted item with `O(1)` time. Therefore we don't have to maintain that DoubleLinkedList and keep track of which item is the oldest.
```
/**
 * @param {number} capacity
 */
var LFUCache = function(capacity) {
  this.keyMap = new Map();
  this.freqMap = new Map();
  this.size = capacity;
  this.minFreq = 1;
};
