# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Use a HashMap to store the key -> {value, frequency} mapping. Use another HashMap which would have the frequency counts as keys and the associated cache keys as a set. Using a LinkedHashSet here would ensure that the order in which items are added to the set is maintained. In case of eviction and mulitple keys having the minimum frequency count, picking the first one from the LinkedHashSet would imply picking the least recently used one.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(1)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class LFUCache {
  int cap;
  int minFreq;
  Map<Integer, int[]> cache;
  Map<Integer, Set<Integer>> freqLists;

  // Updates the value and frequency count in the cache.
  private void helper(int key, int val) {
    int[] a = cache.get(key);
    val = val == -1 ? a[0] : val;
    var freq = a[1];

    cache.put(key, new int[] {val, freq + 1});
    freqLists.putIfAbsent(freq + 1, new LinkedHashSet<>());

    freqLists.get(freq + 1).add(key);
    freqLists.get(freq).remove(key);
    if (freqLists.get(freq).size() == 0) {
      freqLists.remove(freq);
      minFreq = minFreq == freq ? freq + 1 : minFreq;
    }
  }

  public LFUCache(int capacity) {
    cap = capacity;
    minFreq = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
    cache = new HashMap<>();
    freqLists = new HashMap<>();
  }

  public int get(int key) {
    if (!cache.containsKey(key))
      return -1;

    helper(key, -1);
    return cache.get(key)[0];
  }

  public void put(int key, int value) {
    if (!cache.containsKey(key)) {
      if (cap == 0) {
        // The cache is at capacity, find the LFU key and remove it.
        if (minFreq == Integer.MAX_VALUE) return;

        var keyToRemove = freqLists.get(minFreq).iterator().next();
        cache.remove(keyToRemove);
        freqLists.get(minFreq).remove(keyToRemove);

        if (freqLists.get(minFreq).size() == 0)
          freqLists.remove(minFreq);
        cap++;
      }
      // Add the new key to the cache.
      cache.put(key, new int[] {value, 1});
      minFreq = 1;

      freqLists.putIfAbsent(1, new LinkedHashSet<>());
      freqLists.get(1).add(key);
      cap--;
    } else {
      // Update the value of the exisiting key.
      helper(key, value);
    }
  }
}
