# Intuition
We can use a map and a set, set will keep track of frequency and counter whereas map will do the mapping of key-> value.
Set should come as a part of intuition because we want a sorted data structure which can help find us the lFU or LRU element based on counter and frequency.

# Approach
**Have 4 things initialised as public members**

**unordered_map**, with format key-> {val, frequecy, counter}
**set**, with format {frequecy, counter, key}
**cap**, for max capacity of set
**counter**, will start from 0

Now for Get function,
1. we first check if it's in map, if not return -1;
2. if present, then increase frequncy and update counter, by removing prevoius values from map

Now fro put function,
1. we first check if key, present in map, if present, then will update value, frequncy and counter same as Get function method
2. if key not present, then will check if set is full, then will delete first element of set, because set holding freq as 0 index, counter 1 (i.e set is sorted first on basis on frequency and then if frequency same then on basis of counter)
so if freq same, we shall min counter at beginning, delete it and then after deleting, we can insert new key into set.

# Code
```
class LFUCache {
public:
    unordered_map<int, vector<int>> mp;
    set<vector<int>> s;
    int cap;
    //Helps track the latest key on which operation is performed(use for least recently used key)
    int counter = 0;

    LFUCache(int capacity) {
        cap = capacity;
    }

    int get(int key) {
        if(cap == 0 || mp.find(key) == mp.end())
            return -1;

        counter++;
        int val = mp[key][0];
        int fre = mp[key][1];
        int cnt = mp[key][2];
        auto it = s.find({fre, cnt, key});

        //delete the entry in set
        s.erase(it);

        //update key with frequency in map and set
        mp[key] = {val, fre + 1, counter};
        s.insert({fre + 1, counter, key});

        return val;        
    }

    void put(int key, int value) {
        if(cap == 0)
            return;

        counter++;
        //when key is present in Cache
        if(mp.find(key) != mp.end())
        {
            //if present in map, then for sure present in set
            int val = value;
            int fre = mp[key][1];
            int coun = mp[key][2];
            auto it = s.find({fre, coun, key});
            s.erase(it);

            mp[key] = {val, fre + 1, counter};
            s.insert({fre + 1, counter, key});
        }
        //key aint present
        else
        {
            //capacity of cache is reached
            if(s.size() >= cap)
            {
                vector<int> it = *s.begin();
                int key1 = it[2];
                mp.erase(key1);
                s.erase(s.begin());
            }

            mp[key] = {value, 1, counter};
            s.insert({1, counter, key});
        }

        return;
    }
};

